commit/213e5bda)\\n\\n**Env vars added to `buildClaudeQuietEnv`, `getClaudeEnv`, both Dockerfiles, and the merged `~/.claude/settings.json → env`:**\\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_FAST_MODE=1`\\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_FEEDBACK_SURVEY=1` (double-check – confirmed separate from `DISABLE_FEEDBACK_COMMAND`)\\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_MOUSE=1`\\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_ENABLE_AWAY_SUMMARY=0` (explicit disable via the official “enable” toggle)\\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_TOOL_USE_CONCURRENCY=4`\\n\\n**Settings added to the merge helper + Dockerfile baselines (top-level keys, preserving unrelated user settings):**\\n- `includeCoAuthoredBy: false`\\n- `prefersReducedMotion: true`\\n- `showThinkingSummaries: false`\\n- `viewMode: \\\"verbose\\\"`\\n- `spinnerTipsEnabled: false` *(already present; left as-is)*\\n- `attribution: { \\\"commit\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"pr\\\": \\\"\\\" }` *(new — hides Claude attribution on both git commits and PRs per https://code.claude.com/docs/en/settings#attribution-settings)*\\n\\nAll previously-required quiet keys from the issue body are still enforced (`autoMemoryEnabled`, `spinnerTipsEnabled`, `awaySummaryEnabled`, `feedbackSurveyRate` and the six original env vars).\\n\\nRegression test `tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs` was updated to assert every new key/value, preservation of unrelated user-defined attribution/env subkeys, and Dockerfile baking. `npm test` → 41 passed / 0 failed. `npm run lint`, `npm run format:check`, `npm run check:duplication`, `scripts/check-mjs-syntax.sh`, `scripts/validate-changeset.mjs`, `tests/docs-validation.mjs`, and `scripts/check-file-line-limits.sh` (with `node_modules/` moved aside to match CI) all pass.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 📋 Options report — additional env vars & settings to consider\\n\\nI reviewed [`env-vars.md`](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/env-vars) and [`settings.md`](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/settings) end-to-end against our autonomous/Docker use case. Below is everything that **might** be relevant but that I did **not** apply — please select which ones to add and I'll wire them up in a follow-up commit.\\n\\n#### Environment variables\\n\\n| Variable | Suggested value | Why it might fit our autonomous/headless `solve` use | Risk of applying unconditionally |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_ADAPTIVE_THINKING` | `1` | Determinism: Opus/Sonnet 4.6 currently auto-decide thinking depth. Off = fully controlled by our `--max-thinking-budget` / `--effort-level`. | We lose automatic thinking adjustment — may increase cost or reduce quality on tasks where adaptive thinking would have scaled up. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_ATTACHMENTS` | `1` | `solve` never relies on attachments; disables attachment processing path. | Would break any future feature that sends images/files to Claude. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_BACKGROUND_TASKS` | `1` | Prevents Claude from forking bash commands into background tasks that outlive the session. | May slow long-running operations Claude would normally background (docker build, CI poll). |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_BETAS` | `1` | Strips `anthropic-beta` headers for deterministic, published-only behavior. | Cuts off early access to features we may depend on later. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_FILE_CHECKPOINTING` | `1` | We already use git; disables Claude's own per-file checkpoint/undo state. | Would disable `/rewind` / undo safety net. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_NONESSENTIAL_TRAFFIC` | `1` | One-shot switch that implies `DISABLE_TELEMETRY`, `DISABLE_AUTOUPDATER`, `DISABLE_ERROR_REPORTING`, `DISABLE_FEEDBACK_COMMAND`. | Blocks telemetry (already wanted) + error reporting — we lose Anthropic-side crash data from our prod runs. |\\n| `DISABLE_TELEMETRY` | `1` | No OTEL pipeline configured here, avoids spurious exports. | None that I can see — we don't configure telemetry endpoints. |\\n| `DISABLE_AUTOUPDATER` | `1` | Docker image should not silently self-upgrade `claude` CLI at runtime. | None for the container — we pin versions via Dockerfile. |\\n| `DISABLE_ERROR_REPORTING` | `1` | No outbound crash reports from solve sessions. | We stop sending telemetry that helps Anthropic fix bugs that affect us. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_NONSTREAMING_FALLBACK` | `1` | Keeps our stream-json parsing deterministic — no silent fallback on stream hiccup. | On transient stream errors, sessions fail harder instead of degrading. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_OFFICIAL_MARKETPLACE_AUTOINSTALL` | `1` | Headless image should not pull the official plugin marketplace. | We'd need to explicitly opt-in if we ever distribute a managed plugin. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_THINKING` | *(probably no)* | Forces thinking off globally. | We actively use thinking budgets — **don't recommend**. Listed for completeness. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_VIRTUAL_SCROLL` | *(probably no)* | Fullscreen TUI only; irrelevant in `solve`'s non-TTY mode. | No effect for us. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_ENABLE_TASKS` | `1` | Turn on task tracking in `-p` (non-interactive) mode — useful for our logs to surface internal TODO items Claude creates. | Adds output volume. |\\n| `CLAUDE_AUTO_BACKGROUND_TASKS` | `0` or unset | Complement to `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_BACKGROUND_TASKS`. | Same trade-offs. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_SKIP_PROMPT_HISTORY` | `1` | We have our own transcript/log system; skip writing Claude's transcripts. | `/resume` and `cleanupPeriodDays` become moot. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_RESUME_INTERRUPTED_TURN` | *(depends)* | Either force-on or force-off for deterministic restart behavior after a crash mid-turn. | Depends on how we want crash recovery to behave. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_SUBPROCESS_ENV_SCRUB` | `1` | Strips credential-looking env vars from subprocesses Claude spawns (git, gh, etc.). | Could break tools we intentionally pass auth to; must verify `GH_TOKEN`/`GITHUB_TOKEN` aren't stripped. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_NO_FLICKER` / `CLAUDE_CODE_SCROLL_SPEED` / `CLAUDE_CODE_CODE_ACCESSIBILITY` / `CLAUDE_CODE_TMUX_TRUECOLOR` / `CLAUDE_CODE_SYNTAX_HIGHLIGHT` | — | UI-only, we run headless with `--output-format stream-json`. | No effect in non-TTY mode; safe to ignore. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_ENABLE_TELEMETRY` | *(do NOT set)* | Opposite intent. | Don't set. |\\n| `BASH_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MS` / `BASH_MAX_TIMEOUT_MS` / `BASH_MAX_OUTPUT_LENGTH` | *(consider)* | We sometimes wrap long-running commands; tuning these could avoid silent truncation or timeouts. | Needs per-workflow tuning; may conflict with our existing `HIVE_MIND_*` timeouts. |\\n| `API_TIMEOUT_MS` | *(consider)* | Model call timeout ceiling. Default 10min. | Our `HIVE_MIND_CLAUDE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` is 60s — they operate at different layers so probably leave Claude's alone. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_GLOB_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` | *(consider)* | In huge monorepos `Glob` can be slow. Default 20s is usually fine. | None unless we hit a pathological monorepo. |\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_SESSIONEND_HOOKS_TIMEOUT_MS` | *(consider)* | We don't currently ship a SessionEnd hook but may in future. | Low impact today. |\\n\\n#### Settings (`~/.claude/settings.json`)\\n\\n| Key | Suggested value | Why | Risk |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| `autoUpdatesChannel` | `\\\"stable\\\"` | Pins Claude CLI to the “stable” channel (≈1 week behind, skips regressions). Complements `DISABLE_AUTOUPDATER`. | Slightly slower feature adoption. |\\n| `minimumVersion` | *(per release)* | Floor to prevent CI from ever downgrading below a known-good Claude CLI. | Needs maintenance when we bump the floor. |\\n| `cleanupPeriodDays` | `1` | With `CLAUDE_CODE_SKIP_PROMPT_HISTORY=1` this is moot; otherwise shrinks session-file retention. | Loses transcript replay window. |\\n| `disableAllHooks` | `true` | Our `solve` pipeline doesn't rely on user hooks — disabling neutralizes any host-side hook that could interfere. | Blocks any hook we *want* to ship later (e.g. a status-line script). |\\n| `disableAutoMode` | `\\\"disable\\\"` | We always pass explicit `--dangerously-skip-permissions`; makes sure auto-mode isn't picked up from `Shift+Tab`/user settings. | None for non-interactive runs. |\\n| `tui` | `\\\"default\\\"` | Explicit classic renderer; irrelevant in `-p` mode. | None. |\\n| `includeGitInstructions` | `false` | Mirror of `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_GIT_INSTRUCTIONS=1`. Docs: env var wins, but setting the belt makes intent visible in `/status`. | None — we already set the env var. |\\n| `permissions.defaultMode` | `\\\"bypassPermissions\\\"` | Matches `--dangerously-skip-permissions`. Makes the mode audible via `/status`. | We'd need `skipDangerousModePermissionPrompt: true` to avoid the one-time prompt. |\\n| `skipDangerousModePermissionPrompt` | `true` | Pairs with the above. | Makes bypass-permissions frictionless — intended for trusted CI only. |\\n| `outputStyle` | e.g. `\\\"default\\\"` or custom | Pin a specific output style so behavior is identical across hosts. | Need to pick one explicitly. |\\n| `statusLine` | *(skip)* | We run headless; no status line to render. | None. |\\n| `fastModePerSessionOptIn` | `true` | Makes sure fast mode never persists if a user enables it once. Complementary to `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_FAST_MODE=1`. | None. |\\n| `effortLevel` | *(skip — we already pass `CLAUDE_CODE_EFFORT_LEVEL` via env based on the model)* | — | Would conflict with dynamic per-request effort. |\\n| `availableModels` | e.g. `[\\\"opus\\\",\\\"sonnet\\\",\\\"haiku\\\",\\\"opusplan\\\"]` | Lock the Docker image to our known model set. | We already enforce model selection in `config.lib.mjs`. |\\n| `alwaysThinkingEnabled` | *(skip)* | We control thinking per-call. | Would conflict with `--max-thinking-budget`. |\\n\\n#### Notes / caveats\\n\\n- The three already-disabled env vars from the first round (`DISABLE_FEEDBACK_COMMAND=1`, `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_FEEDBACK_SURVEY=1`) are **both** needed — docs confirm they control different things (`/feedback` command vs. session-quality survey).\\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_ENABLE_AWAY_SUMMARY` is an *enable* toggle in the env-vars docs, so `0` is the correct disable value. The mirror setting `awaySummaryEnabled: false` was already in place.\\n- I intentionally did **not** touch `CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_*`, `ANTHROPIC_*`, `CLAUDE_AGENT_SDK_*` — those change authentication/model routing/SDK behavior and shouldn't be defaulted in a quiet-config PR.\\n\\nPlease reply with which items above to apply and I'll land them in a follow-up commit on this branch.\\n\",\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274102693/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"performed_via_github_app\":null},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274104933\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1643#issuecomment-4274104933\",\"issue_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1643\",\"id\":4274104933,\"node_id\":\"IC_kwDOPUU0qc7-wapl\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"konard\",\"id\":1431904,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/konard\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"created_at\"