[2026-04-18T22:04:26.356Z] [INFO]         "text": "Now I understand the full picture. The user wants:\n\n1. **PR Docker check restored** — builds the image but gracefully handles missing `configure-claude` when `HIVE_MIND_VERSION=latest` doesn't have the new bin yet.\n2. **Release Docker builds** — publish npm first, wait, then build with exact version.\n\nThe key challenge: when a PR builds Docker with `HIVE_MIND_VERSION=latest`, and `configure-claude` was JUST added in this PR, the latest npm package might NOT have it yet. So:\n- Dockerfile's `configure-claude` step needs to be optional (not fail build) on PR\n- Release flow needs to enforce presence (exact version pinning)\n\nLet me also check the test file, the scripts, and the current state of the check tests."
[2026-04-18T22:04:26.356Z] [INFO]       }
