[2026-04-18T22:08:14.081Z] [INFO]           "command": "git add .github/workflows/release.yml Dockerfile coolify/Dockerfile scripts/verify-docker-image.sh tests/test-docker-release-order.mjs && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nfix(ci): restore Docker PR build, keep release exact-version enforcement\n\nPR #1643 round-6 feedback: the previous commit replaced the PR Docker build\nwith a static contract test. The maintainer wants Docker to be actually built\nand verified on every PR — but the build must tolerate a `configure-claude`\nbin that hasn't been published to npm yet (since PRs install\n@link-assistant/hive-mind@latest, which predates this very PR).\n\n- Dockerfile / coolify/Dockerfile: branch on HIVE_MIND_VERSION. Release\n  builds (pinned version) strictly require configure-claude; PR builds\n  (latest) skip-with-log if the bin isn't present — solve re-applies the\n  quiet baseline at runtime.\n- scripts/verify-docker-image.sh: same tolerance — warn instead of fail\n  when configure-claude is absent.\n- .github/workflows/release.yml docker-pr-check: restored the real build\n  and in-container verification steps; kept the static release-order\n  contract test before the build so the CI/CD contract stays explicit.\n- tests/test-docker-release-order.mjs: assert PR check now builds and\n  verifies the image; assert Dockerfiles branch on HIVE_MIND_VERSION and\n  gracefully handle a missing configure-claude bin.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\"",
