"body":"## 🤖 Round 6: restore Docker PR check + keep release-order strict\n\nCommit: [`c5207943`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/commit/c5207943). Addresses the latest review comment — the previous commit `dd75288b` over-rotated by replacing the PR Docker build with only a static contract test, which is not what was asked.\n\n### What changed\n\n**`.github/workflows/release.yml` → `docker-pr-check`**\n- Kept the static release-order contract test (`node tests/test-docker-release-order.mjs`) — it's still a useful pre-build guard against regressions of the release-order rule.\n- Restored the real Docker build steps: disk free-up, sandbox base version echo, `docker build --progress=plain -t konard/hive-mind:test .`, and `docker run … bash /verify-docker-image.sh`.\n\n**`Dockerfile` and `coolify/Dockerfile`**\n- The `configure-claude` step now branches on `HIVE_MIND_VERSION`:\n  - **Release builds** (`HIVE_MIND_VERSION=<exact>`) — `configure-claude` must exist and must succeed. Build fails otherwise.\n  - **PR builds** (`HIVE_MIND_VERSION=latest`) — if `configure-claude` isn't in the currently published `@link-assistant/hive-mind@latest` yet (which is the case for this PR, since the bin is introduced here), the build logs and skips the bake-time baseline. `solve` re-applies the quiet baseline at runtime.\n\n**`scripts/verify-docker-image.sh`**\n- Same tolerance: warn instead of fail when `configure-claude` is absent. When present, the verify script still runs `configure-claude --help` and `configure-claude --verify` end-to-end.\n\n**`tests/test-docker-release-order.mjs`**\n- Now asserts the opposite of before: the PR check **must** run `docker build --progress=plain` and `bash /verify-docker-image.sh`. Also asserts both Dockerfiles branch on `HIVE_MIND_VERSION` and tolerate a missing `configure-claude` bin on `latest`.\n- Still asserts the release-order contract: every Docker matrix entry waits on npm, both `docker-publish` and the instant variant pass `HIVE_MIND_VERSION` from the release step, and both depend on their respective release jobs.\n\n### Release-order contract preserved\n1. `main` push → `release` job publishes `@link-assistant/hive-mind@X.Y.Z` to npm.\n2. `docker-publish` waits for npm to serve `X.Y.Z` on every platform matrix entry.\n3. Docker build receives `HIVE_MIND_VERSION=X.Y.Z`, installs that exact version, and runs `configure-claude` strictly.\n\n### PR flow preserved\n1. PR opens → `docker-pr-check` runs contract test, then does a real `docker build .` with `HIVE_MIND_VERSION=latest` (default from `ARG`).\n2. Inside the build, the published `@link-assistant/hive-mind@latest` is installed. If the currently published latest doesn't yet have `configure-claude`, the step logs and skips — this PR itself is what will publish the bin.\n3. `scripts/verify-docker-image.sh` runs inside the container and verifies every tool (base + AI) and tolerantly checks `configure-claude`.\n\n### Local verification\n\n- `node tests/test-docker-release-order.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/test-configure-claude-bin.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/useless-tools.test.mjs` — 22 passed, 0 failed\n- `npm test` — 41 passed, 0 failed\n- `npm run lint` — clean\n- `npm run format:check` — clean\n- `npm run check:duplication` — clean (10.47% ≤ threshold)\n- `bash scripts/check-file-line-limits.sh` — clean\n- `bash scripts/check-mjs-syntax.sh` — clean\n- `node scripts/validate-changeset.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/docs-validation.mjs` — passes\n- `git diff --check` — clean\n- `python3 -c \"import yaml; yaml.safe_load(open('.github/workflows/release.yml'))\"` — valid YAML","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274653751/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null}]
