ts_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2026-04-18T17:26:14Z","updated_at":"2026-04-18T17:26:39Z","body":"I think even better if we set bin reusable command as part of Hive Mind package, so once we get if from latest NPM version for that we should build our docker image after we confirm the npm package is published. Name the command `configure-claude`, so it may be used by our users and system administrators to reset claude code configuration and verify it, so there will be no need to copy files to Dockerfiles themselves, once Hive Mind package with new command is installed. That way it will be useful and reusable for both docker and manually by our users.","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274215641/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274217602","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1643#issuecomment-4274217602","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1643","id":4274217602,"node_id":"IC_kwDOPUU0qc7-w2KC","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2026-04-18T17:27:27Z","updated_at":"2026-04-18T17:27:27Z","body":"🤖 **AI Work Session Started**\n\nStarting automated work session at 2026-04-18T17:27:25.861Z\n\nThe PR has been converted to draft mode while work is in progress.\n\n_This comment marks the beginning of an AI work session. Please wait for the session to finish, and provide your feedback._","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274217602/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274231973","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1643#issuecomment-4274231973","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1643","id":4274231973,"node_id":"IC_kwDOPUU0qc7-w5ql","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2026-04-18T17:36:45Z","updated_at":"2026-04-18T17:36:45Z","body":"## 🤖 Round 4: ship `configure-claude` as a reusable bin command\n\nCommit: [`39657540`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/commit/39657540). Addresses the latest review comment asking for a reusable bin as part of the Hive-Mind npm package so users and sysadmins can reset/verify Claude Code configuration manually — and so Dockerfiles don't have to hand-copy files once the package is globally installed.\n\n### What changed\n\n**New bin** — registered in `package.json`:\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"bin\": {\n    \"configure-claude\": \"./src/configure-claude.mjs\",\n    ...\n  }\n}\n```\n\nInstalled via `bun install -g @link-assistant/hive-mind` (or `npm i -g ...`). Then:\n\n```bash\nconfigure-claude                              # apply quiet defaults to ~/.claude/settings.json\nconfigure-claude --verify                     # non-mutating audit; exits 1 on drift\nconfigure-claude -s /workspace/.claude/settings.json\nconfigure-claude --help\n```\n\n**New shared runner** — [`src/configure-claude.lib.mjs`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4/src/configure-claude.lib.mjs) exposes:\n- `parseConfigureClaudeArgs(argv)` — argv → `{ settingsPath, verify, help }`\n- `resolveSettingsPath(path)` — fallback to `~/.claude/settings.json`\n- `runConfigureClaude({ settingsPath, log })` — apply quiet settings + disallowedTools (reuses canonical maps)\n- `verifyConfigureClaude({ settingsPath })` — non-mutating drift report with per-section missing keys\n- `formatVerifyReport(report)` — human-readable summary\n\nBoth the bin entry point (`src/configure-claude.mjs`) and the Dockerfile wrapper (`scripts/configure-claude-quiet-defaults.mjs`) are thin delegates to this runner.\n\n**Dockerfile / coolify/Dockerfile** continue to COPY a minimal subset (now including `src/configure-claude.lib.mjs`) into a scratch bake dir and invoke the wrapper — so PR builds work before the package is published. Once the image's `bun install -g @link-assistant/hive-mind` step picks up a released version that ships the bin, the same `configure-claude` command is also available on PATH for runtime use. Documented this in both Dockerfiles.\n\n**Tests** — [`tests/test-configure-claude-bin.mjs`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4/tests/test-configure-claude-bin.mjs) (new, wired into `npm test`) covers:\n- package.json `bin` + `build:pre` registration contract\n- `parseConfigureClaudeArgs` for every flag form\n- `resolveSettingsPath` default vs. explicit\n- Help text content (command name, `--verify`, issue reference)\n- `verifyConfigureClaude` drift on missing file\n- End-to-end `configure-claude` apply over a fresh tmp settings.json (every env / settings / attribution / permissions / disallowedTools entry present)\n- `--verify` exits 0 on correct config, exits 1 after tampering\n- Second apply is idempotent\n- `--help` prints usage\n\nThe existing [`tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4/tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs) was extended to also require that both Dockerfiles COPY the new shared runner.\n\n**Changeset** — [`quiet-claude-solve.md`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4/.changeset/quiet-claude-solve.md) was amended to describe the new bin command so the next release includes it.\n\n### Verification\n\n- `node tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/test-configure-claude-bin.mjs` — passes (new)\n- `npm test` — 41 passed, 0 failed\n- `npm run lint` / `npm run format:check` / `npm run check:duplication` — clean\n- `bash scripts/check-file-line-limits.sh` — clean (node_modules moved aside, matching CI)\n- `node scripts/validate-changeset.mjs` — passes\n\n### Why this matches the ask\n\n> \"set bin reusable command as part of Hive Mind package … name the command `configure-claude`, so it may be used by our users and system administrators to reset claude code configuration and verify it\"\n\n- `bin` entry ✅\n- name `configure-claude` ✅\n- reset (default apply) + verify (`--verify`) ✅\n- reusable from users, sysadmins, Dockerfiles, tests — one shared runner ✅\n- ships via `@link-assistant/hive-mind` on npm ✅\n","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274231973/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274243735","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1643#issuecomment-4274243735","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1643","id":4274243735,"node_id":"IC_kwDOPUU0qc7-w8iX","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site