1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2026-04-18T22:02:37Z","updated_at":"2026-04-18T22:02:37Z","body":"I didn't ask to remove docker check (as done in https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1643/commits/dd75288beba5ff60ffefeff7991ca3debae25075), it must be checked in each Pull Request, we can just install latest version of Hive Mind in pr docker check, and for now ignore configuration if configure-claude is not present after installation. But in main branch push we need to first publish the Hive Mind package, verify it was published, and use that exact version for publishing new docker image.\r\n\r\nWe need to ensure all changes are correct, consistent, validated, tested, logged and fully meet each and all discussed requirements (check issue description and all comments in issue and in pull request). Ensure all CI/CD checks pass.","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274644085/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274645439","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1643#issuecomment-4274645439","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1643","id":4274645439,"node_id":"IC_kwDOPUU0qc7-yem_","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2026-04-18T22:03:24Z","updated_at":"2026-04-18T22:03:24Z","body":"🤖 **AI Work Session Started**\n\nStarting automated work session at 2026-04-18T22:03:23.195Z\n\nThe PR has been converted to draft mode while work is in progress.\n\n_This comment marks the beginning of an AI work session. Please wait for the session to finish, and provide your feedback._","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274645439/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274653751","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1643#issuecomment-4274653751","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1643","id":4274653751,"node_id":"IC_kwDOPUU0qc7-ygo3","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2026-04-18T22:08:43Z","updated_at":"2026-04-18T22:08:43Z","body":"## 🤖 Round 6: restore Docker PR check + keep release-order strict\n\nCommit: [`c5207943`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/commit/c5207943). Addresses the latest review comment — the previous commit `dd75288b` over-rotated by replacing the PR Docker build with only a static contract test, which is not what was asked.\n\n### What changed\n\n**`.github/workflows/release.yml` → `docker-pr-check`**\n- Kept the static release-order contract test (`node tests/test-docker-release-order.mjs`) — it's still a useful pre-build guard against regressions of the release-order rule.\n- Restored the real Docker build steps: disk free-up, sandbox base version echo, `docker build --progress=plain -t konard/hive-mind:test .`, and `docker run … bash /verify-docker-image.sh`.\n\n**`Dockerfile` and `coolify/Dockerfile`**\n- The `configure-claude` step now branches on `HIVE_MIND_VERSION`:\n  - **Release builds** (`HIVE_MIND_VERSION=<exact>`) — `configure-claude` must exist and must succeed. Build fails otherwise.\n  - **PR builds** (`HIVE_MIND_VERSION=latest`) — if `configure-claude` isn't in the currently published `@link-assistant/hive-mind@latest` yet (which is the case for this PR, since the bin is introduced here), the build logs and skips the bake-time baseline. `solve` re-applies the quiet baseline at runtime.\n\n**`scripts/verify-docker-image.sh`**\n- Same tolerance: warn instead of fail when `configure-claude` is absent. When present, the verify script still runs `configure-claude --help` and `configure-claude --verify` end-to-end.\n\n**`tests/test-docker-release-order.mjs`**\n- Now asserts the opposite of before: the PR check **must** run `docker build --progress=plain` and `bash /verify-docker-image.sh`. Also asserts both Dockerfiles branch on `HIVE_MIND_VERSION` and tolerate a missing `configure-claude` bin on `latest`.\n- Still asserts the release-order contract: every Docker matrix entry waits on npm, both `docker-publish` and the instant variant pass `HIVE_MIND_VERSION` from the release step, and both depend on their respective release jobs.\n\n### Release-order contract preserved\n1. `main` push → `release` job publishes `@link-assistant/hive-mind@X.Y.Z` to npm.\n2. `docker-publish` waits for npm to serve `X.Y.Z` on every platform matrix entry.\n3. Docker build receives `HIVE_MIND_VERSION=X.Y.Z`, installs that exact version, and runs `configure-claude` strictly.\n\n### PR flow preserved\n1. PR opens → `docker-pr-check` runs contract test, then does a real `docker build .` with `HIVE_MIND_VERSION=latest` (default from `ARG`).\n2. Inside the build, the published `@link-assistant/hive-mind@latest` is installed. If the currently published latest doesn't yet have `configure-claude`, the step logs and skips — this PR itself is what will publish the bin.\n3. `scripts/verify-docker-image.sh` runs inside the container and verifies every tool (base + AI) and tolerantly checks `configure-claude`.\n\n### Local verification\n\n- `node tests/test-docker-release-order.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/test-configure-claude-bin.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/useless-tools.test.mjs` — 22 passed, 0 failed\n- `npm test` — 41 passed, 0 failed\n- `npm run lint` — clean\n- `npm run format:check` — clean\n- `npm run check:duplication` — clean (10.47% ≤ threshold)\n- `bash scripts/check-file-line-limits.sh` — clean\n- `bash scripts/check-mjs-syntax.sh` — clean\n- `node scripts/validate-changeset.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/docs-validation.mjs` — passes\n- `git diff --check` — clean\n- `python3 -c \"import yaml; yaml.safe_load(open('.github/workflows/release.yml'))\"` — valid YAML","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274653751/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274654321","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1643#issuecomment-4274654321","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1643","id":4274654321,"node_id":"IC_kwDOPUU0qc7-ygxx","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2026-04-18T22:09:05Z","updated_at":"2026-04-18T22:09:05Z","body":"## 🤖 Solution Draft Log\nThis log file contains the complete execution trace of the AI solution draft process.\n\n### 💰 Cost: **$2.396387**\n\n### 📊 **Context and tokens usage:**\n\n**Claude Opus 4.7:**\n- 97.6K / 1M (10%) input tokens, 18.8K / 128K (15%) output tokens\n\nTotal: (95.0K + 2.7M cached) input tokens, 18.8K output tokens, $2.395861 cost\n\n**Claude Haiku 4.5:**\n- 16 / 64K (0%) output tokens\n\nTotal: 446 input tokens, 16 output tokens, $0.000526 cost\n\n### 🤖 **Models used:**\n- Tool: Anthropic Claude Code\n- Requested: `opus`\n- **Main model: Claude Opus 4.7** (`claude-opus-4-7`)\n- **Additional models:**\n  *  **Claude Haiku 4.5** (`claude-haiku-4-5-20251001`)\n\n### 📎 **Log file uploaded as Gist** (1520KB)\n- [View complete solution draft log](https://gist.githubusercontent.com/konard/6a169715aed8b9685a095db4f8110beb/raw/b58c036a1daa2786b79ee9657dd55ee1aa310396/solution-draft-log-pr-1776550141003.txt)\n\n---\n*Now working session is ended, feel free to review and add any feedback on the solution draft.*","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274654321/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null}]
[2026-04-18T22:15:18.739Z] [STDOUT] :36:45Z","body":"## 🤖 Round 4: ship `configure-claude` as a reusable bin command\n\nCommit: [`39657540`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/commit/39657540). Addresses the latest review comment asking for a reusable bin as part of the Hive-Mind npm package so users and sysadmins can reset/verify Claude Code configuration manually — and so Dockerfiles don't have to hand-copy files once the package is globally installed.\n\n### What changed\n\n**New bin** — registered in `package.json`:\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"bin\": {\n    \"configure-claude\": \"./src/configure-claude.mjs\",\n    ...\n  }\n}\n```\n\nInstalled via `bun install -g @link-assistant/hive-mind` (or `npm i -g ...`). Then:\n\n```bash\nconfigure-claude                              # apply quiet defaults to ~/.claude/settings.json\nconfigure-claude --verify                     # non-mutating audit; exits 1 on drift\nconfigure-claude -s /workspace/.claude/settings.json\nconfigure-claude --help\n```\n\n**New shared runner** — [`src/configure-claude.lib.mjs`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4/src/configure-claude.lib.mjs) exposes:\n- `parseConfigureClaudeArgs(argv)` — argv → `{ settingsPath, verify, help }`\n- `resolveSettingsPath(path)` — fallback to `~/.claude/settings.json`\n- `runConfigureClaude({ settingsPath, log })` — apply quiet settings + disallowedTools (reuses canonical maps)\n- `verifyConfigureClaude({ settingsPath })` — non-mutating drift report with per-section missing keys\n- `formatVerifyReport(report)` — human-readable summary\n\nBoth the bin entry point (`src/configure-claude.mjs`) and the Dockerfile wrapper (`scripts/configure-claude-quiet-defaults.mjs`) are thin delegates to this runner.\n\n**Dockerfile / coolify/Dockerfile** continue to COPY a minimal subset (now including `src/configure-claude.lib.mjs`) into a scratch bake dir and invoke the wrapper — so PR builds work before the package is published. Once the image's `bun install -g @link-assistant/hive-mind` step picks up a released version that ships the bin, the same `configure-claude` command is also available on PATH for runtime use. Documented this in both Dockerfiles.\n\n**Tests** — [`tests/test-configure-claude-bin.mjs`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4/tests/test-configure-claude-bin.mjs) (new, wired into `npm test`) covers:\n- package.json `bin` + `build:pre` registration contract\n- `parseConfigureClaudeArgs` for every flag form\n- `resolveSettingsPath` default vs. explicit\n- Help text content (command name, `--verify`, issue reference)\n- `verifyConfigureClaude` drift on missing file\n- End-to-end `configure-claude` apply over a fresh tmp settings.json (every env / settings / attribution / permissions / disallowedTools entry present)\n- `--verify` exits 0 on correct config, exits 1 after tampering\n- Second apply is idempotent\n- `--help` prints usage\n\nThe existing [`tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4/tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs) was extended to also require that both Dockerfiles COPY the new shared runner.\n\n**Changeset** — [`quiet-claude-solve.md`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4/.changeset/quiet-claude-solve.md) was amended to describe the new bin command so the next release includes it.\n\n### Verification\n\n- `node tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/test-configure-claude-bin.mjs` — passes (new)\n- `npm test` — 41 passed, 0 failed\n- `npm run lint` / `npm run format:check` / `npm run check:duplication` — clean\n- `bash scripts/check-file-line-limits.sh` — clean (node_modules moved aside, matching CI)\n- `node scripts/validate-changeset.mjs` — passes\n\n### Why this matches the ask\n\n> \"set bin reusable command as part of Hive Mind package … name the command `configure-claude`, so it may be used by our users and system administrators to reset claude code configuration and verify it\"\n\n- `bin` entry ✅\n- name `configure-claude` ✅\n- reset (default apply) + verify (`--verify`) ✅\n- reusable from users, sysadmins, Dockerfiles, tests — one shared runner ✅\n- ships via `@link-assistant/hive-mind` on npm ✅\n","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274231973/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274243735","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1643#issuecomment-4274243735","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1643","id":4274243735,"node_id":"IC_kwDOPUU0qc7-w8iX","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2026-04-18T17:44:11Z","updated_at":"2026-04-18T17:44:11Z","body":"## 🤖 Solution Draft Log\nThis log file contains the complete execution trace of the AI solution draft process.\n\n### 💰 Cost: **$5